antified by Bland-Altman analysis. Conclusions: The proposed\ntechnique enables rapid 3D distortion-free high-resolution imaging and T2*\nmapping. Specifically, 3D-BUDA enables 1-mm isotropic whole-brain imaging in 22\ns at 3 T and 9 s on a 7 T scanner. The combination of multi-echo 3D-BUDA with\nCAIPI acquisition and joint reconstruction enables distortion-free whole-brain\nT2* mapping in 47 s at 1.1x1.1x1.0 mm3 resolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Dec 2022 17:41:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-02"}
